'''''Beatle Quest''''' is a [[text adventure]] video game developed and published by Number 9 Software. Written by Garry Marsh, the game was developed using [[The Quill (software)|''The Quill'']] software program. It was released for the [[Commodore 64]] and [[ZX Spectrum]] computers in 1985.

''Beatle Quest'' received mixed reception from video game critics. The game was commercially successful, debuting at number five on ''[[Commodore User]]''{{'}}s sales charts. ''Beatle Quest'' was originally going be the first game in a trilogy but the plans were abandoned.

